SSH Key-Based Git Authentication

Create SSH Key Directory

mkdir -p ~/.ssh/personal_github_keys
cd ~/.ssh

Generate SSH Key

ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "<GIT_USERNAME>" -f ~/.ssh/personal_github_keys/<SSH_KEY_NAME>

Verify Key

ls -lchrt personal_github_keys/

Start SSH Agent

eval "$(ssh-agent -s)"

Add SSH Key

ssh-add ~/.ssh/personal_github_keys/<SSH_KEY_NAME>

Display Public Key

cat personal_github_keys/<SSH_KEY_NAME>.pub

Add the displayed public key to GitHub.

⸻

SSH Config

Edit config file:

vim config

Add:

#personal github
Host <GITHUB_HOST_ALIAS>
        HostName github.com
        User git
        IdentityFile ~/.ssh/<SSH_KEY_NAME>
#end

